text: Kendektamak () is a rural locality (a selo) in Nikolayevsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 475 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 21 km from Tuymazy, 6 km from Nikolayevka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Kendektamak
